✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: funny for developper

Nice exercise ! 
The difficulty level is great for 'time' and 'code length' modes however it seems very hard in 'reverse' mode.
If you want to submit it for this mode it could be better to display a list of prime number as an input.
Otherwise I agree with 5DN1L comments.

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: Very interesting!

1. Please standardise the variable names:
(a) In Goal section: You must output the Nth Euclid number to the given N.
(b) In Output section: The [[N]]th Euclid number.

2. In my opinion it is clearer to write E(n) = p(n#) + 1.

3. Input section: Suggest changing "number" to "index".

4. Wikipedia page skips the N = 0 case while OEIS page includes the N = 0 case. To me, it is more natural to skip it, because the product of the first 0 prime numbers is undefined to me. If you want to include it, please define the case for N = 0 in the statement.

https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclid_number

https://oeis.org/A006862
